Mafdet's Ledger Houses observe the Vigil by closing maritime cargo filing for the hour — a practical rather than ceremonial suspension.
The closure was formalized after a Kowloon Jade Magistracy delegation pointed out that Mafdet's harbor continued processing during the Vigil, creating a record gap that affected joint manifest dating.
Mafdet's Swift Court treats the Vigil hour as a legal dead zone: no contract executed during the hour is dated to the Vigil period; all filings are stamped to the hour before or after.
The Ledger Houses' relationship to the Vigil is transactional rather than commemorative, which Kowloon's Reckoning faction finds appropriate — at least Mafdet's acknowledgment is structural rather than merely verbal.
The Saltglass Reach Wardens do not observe the Vigil; their cairn-tablet tradition has its own seasonal memory practices.

